comments.body:
I wonder if it's worth it to retain the `.IsWtxid()` interface in the variant-based `GenTxid` class for better readability and shorter code at the call-sites? Should be as simple as e.g.
```
class GenTxid : public std::variant<Txid, Wtxid>
{
public:
    .....
    bool IsWtxid() const { return std::holds_alternative<Wtxid>(*this); }
    .....
}
```

